<p class="summary">*Slow Seasons is a book by Rosie Steer about how reconnecting with Nature and living more slowly, helped her recover from depression and live more fully.*</p>

<p>The book goes through the Seasons via the Celtic calendar, with wonderful ideas of seasonal activities and a telling of the changes in Nature at that time. I absolutely loved it! Rosie lives a life a lot of us who like cottage-core would probably dream of.</p>

<p>She has so much access to gardens and countryside, as well as the time to go foraging, it is genuinely amazing. The book whisks you away into this idyllically quaint rural world, in a way a fantasy fiction might. It&rsquo;s very sweet, wonderfully charming escapism, with threads of real applications that we can put into our lives.</p>

